sql:
SELECT COUNT(claim_id) AS claim_count
FROM claims
WHERE age_band_id IN (
    SELECT age_band_id
    FROM age_bands
    WHERE max_age > 30 OR min_age < 50
) AND total_claim_value > (
    SELECT AVG(total_claim_value)
    FROM claims
);

external_knowledge:
- The `age_band_name` refers to the name of the age band, such as "16-24";
- The `total_claim_value` is measured in millions of pounds;
- The overall average total claim value is the mean of all claim values in the `claims` table.

